  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">George Thompson describes four anti-slavery meetings in New Bedford, at which he and William Lloyd Garrison were the speakers. Thompson comments: &quot;The last gathering was a bumper.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On the first page of the letter, there are two layers of writing, lengthwise and crosswise.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes an envelope with a seal. The delivery address is: &quot;Miss Anne Warren Weston, (Captain Weston&apos;s), Weymouth, Mass.&quot; With a notation in the lower left corner: &quot;from G.T.&quot;</subfield>
